\f1\fs29\fsmilli14667  David and Rehoboam and \'92Adr\'e2m\'ee, his son by a Greek slave, and then he shows him how Joseph, and Moses, and Joshua, were types of Christ, and how Christ should spring from Solomon\'92s seed and redeem mankind. In Chap. 68 the Angel prophesies concerning the Virgin Mary, and narrates to Solomon the history of the Pearl which passed from the body of Adam to Abraham, Isaac, Jacob, Perez, Jesse, David, Solomon, Rehoboam, and Joachim, who passed it into the body of \uc0\u7716 anna, the mother of the Virgin Mary. Finally, the Angel told Solomon that Michael would remain with the Tabernacle in Ethiopia, and he (Gabriel) with Rehoboam, and Uriel with \'92Adr\'e2m\'ee. And Solomon gave thanks to God, and asked the Angel when the Saviour would come (Chap. 69), and the Angel replied, \'93After three and thirty generations.\'94 When the Angel told him that the Israelites would crucify the Saviour, and be scattered over the face of the earth, Solomon wept, and the words of his lamentations fill the rest of Chap. 69.\
Solomon died, and Zadok anointed Rehoboam king, and when he had laid a wooden tablet{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://76E898C0-615E-4310-BB90-A04A3587A01A"}}{\fldrslt ,}} with Solomon\'92s name inserted upon it, upon the Tabernacle, the people set him on the royal mule and cried, Hail! Long live the royal father (Chap. 70). Owing to Rehoboam\'92s arrogant behaviour the people revolted, and they armed themselves and went to B\'eath Efr\'e2t\'e2, and made Jeroboam, the son of Nebat, king over them. From Rehoboam to Joachim, the grandfather of Christ, were forty-one generations. The Virgin Mary and Joseph the carpenter were akin, each being descended from David, King of Israel (Chap. 71).\
